  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><strong>DAY 1 | ARRIVAL &amp; NORTHERN LIGHTS SEARCH</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p>Your Inghams Representative will welcome you at Evenes Airport and take you by coach to the Sortland Hotel. After settling in, join us for an orientation walk around the town, just to get your bearings.</p>
<p>After dinner at the hotel, we head out on a guided evening excursion into the surrounding area in search of the Northern Lights. Our guide knows the best spots to see this amazing natural phenomenon and will be on hand to assist with taking the best photographs so make sure to bring your camera and tripod!</p>
<p><img src="/media/13052879/whale-watching.jpg" alt="Whale watching" width="727" height="347" rel="840,401" /></p>
<p><strong>DAY 2 | WHALE WATCHING &amp; NATIONAL COASTAL SCENIC ROUTE<br /></strong></p>
<p>After breakfast at the hotel, you’ll set off on a memorable day trip to the small town of Åndenes, at the very tip of Andøy Island and ‘home of the whales’. After a guided tour of the whale museum, you will set out on a 3 hour expedition out into the ocean in search of whales. You are most likely to see sperm whales at this time of year, but other species may also be spotted – it all depends on the migration of the herring! The knowledgeable boat crew have detection equipment to give you the absolute best chances of seeing these impressive mammals. If you prefer, you can choose to go out on RIB boat to get even closer (must be pre-booked, supplement of £25 applies). Thermal suits are available free of charge locally for either trip.</p>
<p>After a buffet lunch, we head back to Sortland via the spectacular National Tourist Route, recognised as one of the most beautiful routes in Norway, which stretches 58km down the coast from Åndenes to Bjørnskinn. Guided throughout, we will pass the stunning white sandy beaches of the unique village of Bleik, the little-known fishing village of Nordmæla, and the interesting rock formations of Bukkekjerka. Dinner tonight is taken at your hotel.</p>
<p><img src="/media/13052874/reindeer-farm.jpg" alt="Sami reindeer farm" width="727" height="347" rel="840,401" /></p>
<p><strong>DAY 3 | SÁMI, REINDEER, SALMON &amp; SEARCH FOR THE <strong>NORTHERN LIGHTS</strong><br /></strong></p>
<p>This morning, you head to an authentic working reindeer farm to meet a traditional Sámi family and their herd. After meeting the reindeer, you’ll cosy up in a traditional ‘Lavvu’ tent with a hot drink by the open fire to hear and learn about the Sámi culture and way of life.</p>
<p>For lunch, you’ll head to nearby Blokken and its ‘Akvakultur’ fish farm. One of Norway’s most important renowned products, you’ll get to try some of the Norwegian salmon enjoyed by millions worldwide every day for its high quality and great taste – straight from the fjords, it will probably be the freshest lunch you will ever have. You’ll also enjoy a guided tour of the exhibition and boat trip to the salmon pens before heading back to the Sortland for the late afternoon.</p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">After dinner the hotel, we head out again on a guided ‘In Search of the Northern Lights’ excursion for another opportunity to see the Aurora Borealis.
<p><strong>DAY 4 (for 3-night breaks Sun-Weds) | RETURN TO UK</strong></p>
<p>Depart late morning for your return flight to UK.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 4 (for 4-night breaks Weds-Sun) | NYKSUND FISHING VILLAGE<br />&amp; FAREWELL CONCERT<br /></strong></p>
<p>After a leisurely breakfast, we head out north-east on a guided scenic round trip taking the coastal roads all the way to the old fishing village of Nyksund, located on the outer edges of the region and which has a varied and interesting history. You’ll discover its unique story and also enjoy a delicious lunch at a traditional restaurant.</p>
<p>In the evening, you will head out this time south to the coastal town of Melbu. Aperitifs will be served as you take your seats for a private classical concert in the unique setting inside one of the former fishing oil tanks, now<br />known as the ‘Royal Neptun Hall’. After the concert, we will head inside for a delicious meal, cooked in an open kitchen and using local produce for a memorable last evening of your Norwegian adventure.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 5 (for 4-night breaks Weds-Sun) | RETURN TO UK</strong></p>
<p>Guests on our 4-night adventure have the morning at leisure before the coach leaves for Evenes Airport and your homebound flight.</p>
</div>]]></thingsToDo>
